functions.label: apiCanAccessViewMode
description: A type guard which can be used to determine if a given API has access to a view mode, its own or from its parent.

functions.label: apiHasParentApi
description: A type guard which checks whether or not a given API has a parent API.

functions.label: apiIsOfType
signature: <T extends string = string>(api: unknown, typeToCheck: string) => api is

functions.label: apiPublishesDisabledActionIds
description:
A type guard which checks whether or not a given API publishes Disabled Action IDs.  This can be used
to programatically limit which actions are available on a per-API basis.

functions.label: apiPublishesSavedObjectId
description: A type guard which can be used to determine if a given API publishes a saved object id.

functions.label: apiPublishesViewMode
description: A type guard which can be used to determine if a given API publishes a view mode.

functions.label: getInheritedViewMode
description:
A function which will get the view mode from the API or the parent API. if this api has a view mode AND its
parent has a view mode, we consider the APIs version the source of truth.

functions.label: hasEditCapabilities
description: A type guard which determines whether or not a given API is editable.

functions.label: useBatchedPublishingSubjects
description:
Batches the latest values of multiple publishing subjects into a single object. Use this to avoid unnecessary re-renders.
You should avoid using this hook with subjects that your component pushes values to on user interaction, as it can cause a slight delay.

functions.label: useBlockingError
description: Gets this API's fatal error as a reactive variable which will cause re-renders on change.

functions.label: useDataLoading
description: Gets this API's data loading state as a reactive variable which will cause re-renders on change.

functions.label: useDataViews
description: Gets this API's data views as a reactive variable which will cause re-renders on change.

functions.label: useDefaultPanelDescription
description: A hook that gets this API's default panel description as a reactive variable which will cause re-renders on change.

functions.label: useDefaultPanelTitle
description: A hook that gets this API's default title as a reactive variable which will cause re-renders on change.

functions.label: useDisabledActionIds
description: Gets this API's disabled action IDs as a reactive variable which will cause re-renders on change.

functions.label: useHidePanelTitle
description: A hook that gets this API's hide panel title setting as a reactive variable which will cause re-renders on change.

functions.label: useInheritedViewMode
description:
A hook that gets a view mode from this API or its parent as a reactive variable which will cause re-renders on change.
if this api has a view mode AND its parent has a view mode, we consider the APIs version the source of truth.

functions.label: useLocalFilters
description: A hook that gets this API's local filters as a reactive variable which will cause re-renders on change.

functions.label: useLocalQuery
description: A hook that gets this API's local query as a reactive variable which will cause re-renders on change.

functions.label: useLocalTimeRange
description: A hook that gets this API's local time range as a reactive variable which will cause re-renders on change.

functions.label: usePanelDescription
description: A hook that gets this API's panel description as a reactive variable which will cause re-renders on change.

functions.label: usePanelTitle
description: A hook that gets this API's panel title as a reactive variable which will cause re-renders on change.

functions.label: usePublishingSubject
description:
Declares a publishing subject, allowing external code to subscribe to react state changes.
Changes to state fire subject.next

interfaces.label: HasEditCapabilities
description:
An interface which determines whether or not a given API is editable.
In order to be editable, the api requires an edit function to execute the action
a getTypeDisplayName function to display to the user which type of chart is being
edited, and an isEditingEnabled function.
